- 'Alice Smith' is the full name of the owner; 
- 'Stakes' is a type of high-profile horse racing event; 
- 'Fast' track condition refers to a dry and even racing surface; 
- 'Bris Speed' is a rating system used to evaluate a horse's performance; 
- 'Top three performances' refer to the performances ranked 1 to 3.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(horse_id) AS number_of_horses_in_race
FROM races_horses
WHERE race_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(horse_id) AS number_of_horses
FROM ownerships
WHERE owner_id = 1;
